div.h1: x86 Boot Sequence: BIOS to C Entry
div.p: Power-on Protected Mode Kernel Entry Point

ol.li:
POST (Power-On Self-Test)
Memory test
Hardware init
PCI enumeration

div.p: 0x0000 - IVT (1KB) 0x0400 - BDA (256B) BIOS Data Area 0x0500 - Available 0x7C00 - MBR Load Target 0xA000 - VGA Memory 0xF0000 - BIOS ROM 0xFFFFF - ROM End
0x7C00 - Stage1 code (running here) 0x8000 - Stage2 load addr (target for read) 0x10000 - Kernel load addr
Offset 0x08: Kernel Code Descriptor: 0x00CF9A00 Base: 0x00000000, Limit: 4GB Access: Exec/Read, Ring 0
Offset 0x10: Kernel Data Descriptor: 0x00CF9200 Base: 0x00000000, Limit: 4GB Access: Read/Write, Ring 0
0x7C00 - Stage1 (still present) 0x8000 - Stage2 code -> 0x8200 - GDT (24 bytes) [Null][Code][Data]
Pipeline flush required! After CR0.PE=1, CPU is in protected mode but CS still has real-mode base. Must do FAR JUMP immediately to:

div.p: CS = 0x08 (base=0, limit=4GB) DS = 0x10 (base=0, limit=4GB) ES = 0x10 (base=0, limit=4GB) SS = 0x10 (base=0, limit=4GB)

0x000000 - IVT (unused in PM) 0x0007C00 - Stage1 (can be reused) 0x0008000 - Stage2 bootloader 0x0008200 - GDT (24 bytes) 0x0009000 - Stack top (grows down) 0x0010000 - Kernel (ELF loaded) .text .rodata .data .bss 0x00A0000 - VGA buffer (0xB8000)
